# K-HARDEN-8: Cursor cold-start entry (legacy .cursorrules format).
#
# Modern Cursor reads `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (see 000-agents-alignment.mdc).
# This .cursorrules file is kept as fallback for older Cursor versions.
# Per Cursor 2026 docs, .cursorrules is deprecated; migrate to `.cursor/rules/`.

# Read order (cold start)
- AGENTS.md (canonical shared agent contract — read first)
- HARNESS_PLAYBOOK.md (full operating manual)
- skills/SUBAGENT_HARNESS.md (subagent dispatch template)
- constitution.md (axioms)

# Hard rules (enforced by hooks)
- PR-only: never `git push origin main`. Create feature branch + PR.
  Direct push blocked at GitHub server-side + local `.git/hooks/pre-push`.
- No wildcard staging: never `git add .` or `git add -A`. Explicit paths only.
- No sidecar contamination: handover/evidence/dev_self_hosting/dev_*/
  must never be staged.
- Restricted surfaces (AGENTS.md §6) require per-atom architect §8.

# Coding style
- First-principles architecture (skills/KARPATHY_ARCHITECT.md)
- Transparent data flow, no Manager/Factory/Engine (skills/KARPATHY_SIMPLE_CODE.md)
- Surgical changes only

# Setup (one time per clone)
- bash scripts/install_hooks.sh
- bash scripts/setup_branch_protection.sh

# AGENTS.md is canonical. Conflicts → AGENTS.md wins.
